defaultAbout:default The County Councils Network (CCN) 
defaultrepresents 37 English local authorities that serve counties. CCN membership includes both upper tier and u
defaultnitary authorities who together have over 2500 councillors and serve 23 million people (46% of the population) across 85% of England.  CCN develops policy, shares best practice and makes representations to government on behalf of this significant proportio
defaultn of the country outside the big conurbations. 
defaultCCN is a member-led organisation which works on an inclusive and all party basis and seeks to make representations to government which can be supported by all member authorities.
